1
00:00:01,640 --> 00:00:03,569
-Can you believe it, kids?

2
00:00:03,569 --> 00:00:07,211
First, a Juicy Toobin concert,
then a meet-and-greet?

3
00:00:07,211 --> 00:00:10,762
Just a 5-hour drive
for a 30-minute show.

4
00:00:10,762 --> 00:00:12,057
I ain't mad.

5
00:00:12,057 --> 00:00:15,221
-Okay, guys, my name is Craig.

6
00:00:15,221 --> 00:00:18,384
I am the human helper
on the Toobin tour.

7
00:00:18,384 --> 00:00:20,933
Now, who's ready
to meet the Juicy Toobins?

8
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:22,674
-Me!
-Me!

9
00:00:22,674 --> 00:00:25,005
-When I say, "Juicy,"
you say, "Toobin."

10
00:00:25,005 --> 00:00:28,074
-Juicy!
-Toobin!
-Juicy!
-Toobin!

11
00:00:28,074 --> 00:00:31,731
-And when I say back up,
you back the hell up.

12
00:00:34,282 --> 00:00:37,581
You back the hell up.

13
00:00:38,246 --> 00:00:41,860
I'm security.
You don't need to know my name.

14
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:46,526
Listen closely.
If you want to meet
the Toobins,
you got to follow the rules.

15
00:00:46,526 --> 00:00:49,076
-Um. Sure, man. Yeah.
Whatever.

16
00:00:49,076 --> 00:00:51,532
-One, the Toobins owe you
nothing.

17
00:00:51,532 --> 00:00:54,828
They don't owe you a picture.
They don't owe you a hug.

18
00:00:54,828 --> 00:00:57,956
And they certainly don't
owe you a Toobin Tango.

19
00:00:57,956 --> 00:01:02,728
Two, keep in mind,
the Toobins are exhausted.

20
00:01:02,728 --> 00:01:06,661
They are performing
three shows a week.

21
00:01:06,661 --> 00:01:08,469
They are spent.

22
00:01:08,469 --> 00:01:10,502
-It's like barely any shows.

23
00:01:10,502 --> 00:01:13,610
-And three, if you move
too quick on a Toobin,

24
00:01:13,610 --> 00:01:16,947
I will kick you
all the way to Guam.

25
00:01:16,947 --> 00:01:20,229
Do I make myself clear?
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

26
00:01:20,229 --> 00:01:22,738
-I said,
do I make myself clear?!

27
00:01:22,738 --> 00:01:24,917
-Yes!
-Yes!
-Good.

28
00:01:24,917 --> 00:01:29,187
-Hey, man,
it's a children's concert.
Maybe just take it down a notch?

29
00:01:29,187 --> 00:01:31,998
-What'd you say, fella?
Huh?
-I'm just saying, man.

30
00:01:31,998 --> 00:01:33,365
-What are you doing?

31
00:01:33,365 --> 00:01:36,465
-...your kid
gets a Toobin Sleeve.
-What? Oh, my God!

32
00:01:37,202 --> 00:01:39,766
-That's not my kid.

33
00:01:40,146 --> 00:01:44,873
-If you guys think I'm playing
around, I assure you I am not.

34
00:01:44,873 --> 00:01:48,392
-Stomp, stomp, stomp.
Who could that be?

35
00:01:48,392 --> 00:01:52,677
It's Mama Toobin
and her famous cinnamon rolls!

36
00:01:52,677 --> 00:01:56,238
-Hi, kids.
Good thing
I wore my boogie shoes.

37
00:01:56,238 --> 00:01:57,889
Come here, kids. Let's dance.

38
00:01:57,889 --> 00:02:01,396
-Back up, back up!
Back up, back up!

39
00:02:01,396 --> 00:02:04,435
-Back up! Step to the side!

40
00:02:04,908 --> 00:02:08,408
-Everyone say,
"Bye-bye, Mama Toobin."

41
00:02:08,408 --> 00:02:11,760
-Bye-bye, Mama Toobin!

42
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:15,592
-All right,
we've established one thing.
You kids don't listen.

43
00:02:15,592 --> 00:02:18,134
What's your name?
-Adeline.

44
00:02:18,134 --> 00:02:22,941
-Adeline, you are at a 10.
I need you to take it down
to a 4.

45
00:02:22,941 --> 00:02:26,342
You, what's your deal?
-I'm Josie.

46
00:02:26,342 --> 00:02:28,538
-You're a vulture, Josie.

47
00:02:28,538 --> 00:02:32,808
Yeah. You're a little vulture.
I can smell it.

48
00:02:32,808 --> 00:02:38,360
You take and you take until
the Toobins have nothing left.

49
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,542
-Hey!
-You, Josie!

50
00:02:39,542 --> 00:02:40,868
-No.
-Vulture!

51
00:02:40,868 --> 00:02:43,635
-Look. They were just dancing
with her, man.

52
00:02:43,635 --> 00:02:47,400
-Oh, hey. Yeah, buddy?
One man's dance party is
another man's stampede.

53
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,456
I learned that serving in Iraq.

54
00:02:49,456 --> 00:02:55,427
-You served in Iraq?
-Yes. I was a server in Iraq.
-Oh.

55
00:02:55,427 --> 00:02:59,285
-I served at
the Baghdad Cheesecake Factory.

56
00:02:59,285 --> 00:03:02,434
Number-one Cheesecake Factory
in the Middle East.

57
00:03:02,434 --> 00:03:04,751
That's where I cut my teeth
in crowd control.

58
00:03:04,751 --> 00:03:07,011
-What are you talking about,
man?

59
00:03:07,011 --> 00:03:12,297
-Stomp, stomp, stomp, kids.
Here comes Papa Toobin.

60
00:03:12,297 --> 00:03:16,332
-Who's ready to shake,
shimmy, and do the Toobin Tango?

61
00:03:16,332 --> 00:03:17,636
Come here, friends.

62
00:03:17,636 --> 00:03:21,483
-Back up, back up,
back up, back up!

63
00:03:23,566 --> 00:03:26,456
-Hey, you little kid.
You're like a little mosquito
on there.

64
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:28,300
You get off!

65
00:03:28,300 --> 00:03:30,788
-Oh, my God!
-Hey!

66
00:03:31,679 --> 00:03:34,355
-Put him down! Put him down!

67
00:03:37,062 --> 00:03:40,986
-I wasn't gonna throw him.
I know how
to safely throw a child, okay?

68
00:03:40,986 --> 00:03:42,427
I was not gonna throw him.

69
00:03:42,427 --> 00:03:45,470
-Everyone say,
"Night-night, Papa Toobin."

70
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:48,830
-Night-night, Papa Toobin!

71
00:03:48,830 --> 00:03:51,645
-Well, that was hell.

72
00:03:52,018 --> 00:03:54,500
Adults in the room, you guys,

73
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:58,864
I'm sure a big chunk of you
are on the spectrum.

74
00:03:58,864 --> 00:04:01,734
-You what?
-Excuse me?

75
00:04:01,734 --> 00:04:07,832
-And I can assure you,
I am on the spectrum, as well.

76
00:04:13,672 --> 00:04:18,169
I'm on the spectrum
of having it to not having it.

77
00:04:18,169 --> 00:04:20,994
Except instead of a spectrum,
it's a switch.

78
00:04:20,994 --> 00:04:22,504
And, honey, you just flipped it.

79
00:04:22,504 --> 00:04:25,997
-Dude, relax.
For the last time, relax.

80
00:04:25,997 --> 00:04:28,015
-Relax?
Boom!

81
00:04:28,015 --> 00:04:31,821
-Oh, no!
-Toobin Sleeve.
Toobin Sleeve.

82
00:04:32,942 --> 00:04:34,467
-Hey!

83
00:04:34,467 --> 00:04:36,962
-Watch it, sister. At the
Baghdad Cheesecake Factory,

84
00:04:36,962 --> 00:04:39,740
I was doing four
to five Toobin Sleeves a day.

85
00:04:39,740 --> 00:04:44,563
-Okay. If you were using them
in Baghdad,
then why are they called
Toobin Sleeves?

86
00:04:44,563 --> 00:04:48,105
-Bitch! I know you ain't poking
holes right now.

87
00:04:48,105 --> 00:04:50,946
-Okay, okay.

88
00:04:51,908 --> 00:04:57,087
Okay, kids, this is the moment
you've all been waiting for.

89
00:04:57,087 --> 00:05:01,927
He's cute, he's cuddly,
and he loves asparagus.

90
00:05:01,927 --> 00:05:03,088
It's...

91
00:05:03,088 --> 00:05:05,136
-Hold, hold, hold, hold, hold.

92
00:05:05,136 --> 00:05:07,276
Baby Toobin is about
to come out.

93
00:05:07,276 --> 00:05:11,661
And I know you feral, little
effers want to go nuts on him,

94
00:05:11,661 --> 00:05:14,396
but that will happen
over my dead body.

95
00:05:14,396 --> 00:05:19,862
-Everyone, give it up
for Baby Toobin!

96
00:05:19,862 --> 00:05:23,584
-Hi, kids.
Who wants a Toobin toy?

97
00:05:23,584 --> 00:05:26,099
-Me!
-Me!
-Here you go!

98
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:28,749
-Hey! Stop it!

99
00:05:28,749 --> 00:05:31,074
Do not feed the beast!

100
00:05:31,074 --> 00:05:33,414
Dear God!

